{
  "stem": "1061.4",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Because I mean, if we had lice-- I mean a woman like this, this SS woman, she probably would spit on me if she ever-- or kill me if she ever saw lice on me, you see.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So they gave us under the barracks-- where the kitchen was and all that-- they gave us a place to live.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "There were bunks there, but we did not-- we were not allowed to sleep in the regular barracks.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Because after all, you know, if you come to clean her office and then something would you bring some sicknesses from the others, I mean, you know.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So this was Retzow.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And this is now February, 1945.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And some people were already liberated, those who stayed behind in Poland.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And for us, there was no end.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And I couldn't even imagine how liberation would come.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I, I couldn't even-- to put it in the most far-fetched [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] picture.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "You know, the bombs started falling, so we knew that something was now happening, which we're hoping will really be the end, that whether they kill us with the bombs is better than everything.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Because I mean, we might yet be sent again and sent again.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And who knows where we will finally end up, right?",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But the point is that-- you-- you asked me before if I had a plan.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I not only had no plan, I had not even the imagination to conjure up a picture of how will it all come about.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "You know, you're a child and you read books, and there are-- you know, when people get liberated, there are parades, and the band is playing, and the flags are flying, and people are throwing flowers.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It didn't fit the picture.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And then I said to myself, maybe we'll just-- they will just march us out.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Well, that wouldn't fit the picture.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Because there has to be some shooting going on.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And then maybe the bombs will fall.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Whatever it was, I absolutely couldn't imagine.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "But the fact is, I was with my sisters.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "We all three lived of us in that unit underneath.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "The bombs were falling.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "They all sent us down, you know, to sit out the air raid, which we did.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And we were glad of it.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Because now they-- the Germans we scared, too.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "So you see, now when we suffered, we at least saw that they have something to worry about, too.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "Although, by that time, you know, if the bomb fell, we never had any idea what happened to mother.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "We, we didn't know about father at all.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "There were just the three of us.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "But we were together.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And if the bombs were to take us, it really would have been fine, in the sense that all the horror that we went through, we certainly could not to go through again.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And we had no idea if the war is at an end or in the middle or whatever it is.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] I, in my-- in my small child's mind was very glad to see that the German women that we served, that they were as scared as, as any of us.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And I said to myself, well, maybe they'll now know what it feels like to, to live with fear every second of your life and-- and to anticipate greater horror, which is the only thing that the experience taught us, you know.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "That the more-- the only thing you can expect is more horror of another kind, you see.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Not necessarily it's the same that you went before.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] Could we stop at this point for a minute?",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We're almost-- we're almost done.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes?",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "All right.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, we were not liberated.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Because as it turns out, with the bombing and all, that camp had to be evacuated.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So you see, one more evacuation.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Except this is not January, and there is no snow.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "The month is April, 1945, end of April, 1945.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We are lined up again, counted again.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And those of us who were personal maids to the SS women have to carry their things, their rucksacks.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "We didn't take anything of our own, but we had to carry their stuff.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And we were marched out of the camp somewhere, onto a road that was completely overrun with people of every kind-- of Germans, of, of German soldiers and German in uniform, out of uniform, and tanks and-- and horses, and the farmers with cows, and, and, and Polish POWs and Polish farmhands who worked the-- Polish, I meant Christian.",
      "word_count": 59
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "The Christian Poles who were working the farms in-- in Germany during the war.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Slave labor, also, in-- of another kind, because they lived on the places where they worked.",
      "word_count": 16
    }
  ],
